# Create Your Own Fabric App

This guide will help you replicate the Minecraft Warehouse Operations Copilot app in your own environment using GitHub Copilot and connect it to your own Fabric semantic model.

---

## Part 1: Generate the App with GitHub Copilot

### Prerequisites
1. **Node.js (v22)**: Download from https://nodejs.org/dist/v22.22.2/node-v22.22.2-x64.msi
2. **GitHub Copilot CLI**: Refer to https://github.com/github/copilot-cli
3. **Playwright CLI**: Run `npm install -g @playwright/cli@latest`
4. **Azure CLI**: Install from https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/cli/azure/install-azure-cli?view=azure-cli-latest

### Step 1: Create a New Repository

```bash
# Create a new folder for your app
mkdir my-fabric-app
cd my-fabric-app
git init
```

### Step 2: Copy and Paste This Prompt into GitHub Copilot

Open Terminal in your repo folder and run:
```bash
